Eight laboratory works (24 hours) are designed to practice PC assembling, software installation and system debugging methods.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The main goal of the cource is to give the ICT specialist a practical experience about PC assembling, repairing and device configuration.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing this course, the students are able to: 1. assemble a personal computer; 2. build a local network (incl configuring wireless network) and bring out how different devices affect network's throughput; 3. create different file systems, install an operating system, and create virtual machines; 4. articulate properties of different types of storage devices and computer bus interfaces; 5. assess the effects of various parameters to the computer performance; 6. compose and format practical assignment reports in accordance to the given requirements (incl. correct Estonian grammar).
